uniol.apt.analysis.cycles.lts

Class PVwithSequence

  • java.lang.Object
    • uniol.apt.analysis.cycles.lts.PVwithSequence

  • public class PVwithSequence
extends java.lang.Object
    A datastructure for saving a parikh vector and a sequence. It is not checked if they are belonging together but it is intended.

    Manuel Gieseking

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public static PVwithSequence add(PVwithSequence first,
                                 PVwithSequence second)
        Adds to given PVwithSequences together to a new one. That means their sequences will be concatenate and their parikh vectors added.
        Parameters:
        first - - the first parikh vector and sequence to add. The left side of the concatenation.
        second - - the second parikh vector and sequence to add. The right side of the concatenation.
        Returns:
        a new generated parikh vector with sequence, with the addition of the parikh vectors and concatenation of the sequences of the given parikh vectors with there sequences.

      • glue

        public static PVwithSequence glue(PVwithSequence first,
                                  PVwithSequence second)
        Glues to given PVwithSequences together to a new one. That means their parikh vectors will be added and there sequences will be concatenated, but the last component of the first sequence is replaced by the first component of the second sequence.
        Parameters:
        first - - the first parikh vector and sequence to glue. The left side of the concatenation.
        second - - the second parikh vector and sequence to glue. The right side of the concatenation.
        Returns:
        a new generated parikh vector with sequence, with the addition of the parikh vectors and gluing concatenation of the sequences of the given parikh vectors with there sequences.
